commit.message: Merge release 4.0 into develop.
Back to development: 4.1

Revert "Update versions in README."

This reverts commit 1184a3c7100773e14fade74b4cd0ad7f94b99b5f.
Release 4.0.
Add special credits for major changes to the change log.

Readme: Update Donation link.

- Point to `funding` page on homepage.
- Remove bountysource, as this has killed our team without notice.
- Remove bitcoin, since crypto currency does not pay your rent not servers.

Readme: Add section pointing to Changelog.

This is a preparation for the next change.

setup: Fix long-description for PyPI.

Basically: Only use the Readme.rst as the long-description.
Also explicitly set the long-description-content-type.

PyPI now checks whether the uploaded `long-description` renders with the
selected long-description-content-type, and is quite strict on this: It does
not support Sphiny, but only plain reStructuredText.

While we could add more dummies for Sphinx-roles used in the change-log (which
we already had for e.g. `issue`), this failed with »Unknown directive type
"toctree"«. So I decided to no longer include the change-log into the
long-description, but instead add a section to the Readme (which is the base
of the long-description, pointing to the change-log.

I also enhanced the Relead descriptoion in the wiki to include running `twine
check` to catch errors early.
Requirements: Update changed package name.
doc: Update "What's New This Release" section for release 4.0.
doc: Rebuild man-pages for release 4.0.
Update versions in README.
Update CREDITS for release 4.0.
Preparing release 4.0.
Fix wrong news-entry filenames.
Recompile Bootloaders for Darwin, Linux and Windows.

Bootloader build: Vagrantfile: Stop Cortana.

Not sure whether this works, but worth a try.
Bootloader build: Vagrantfile: Fix downloading choco via TLS 1.2
tests: skip the hook-order tests; they need redoing.
